<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>An 11-year-old Gold Coast girl has been missing for 10 days and police hold serious concerns about her welfare.</p>

<p>Laine-Ella Hyland hasn't been heard from or seen since she was at a Southport address on August 24, police say.</p>

<p>An Amber Alert has been issued calling on public help to find her, with police seriously concerned about her wellbeing.</p>

<p>She was previously seen leaving her Main Beach home at 8.30pm on August 18.</p>

<p>Laine-Ella is Caucasian, slim and about 150cm tall with shoulder-length blonde hair and blue eyes. She was last seen wearing a grey hoodie and black shorts.</p>
